Waive reading of the information.  Defense entered NGP.  Court entered NGP on the defendant's behalf.  Set for PTC 11/2. STC date set for 11/21 @ 3 pm.

10:27 AM Defendant Skipper D. Johnson in court, in custody from JCJ.  Attorney Lucas Swank appeared by video for Skipper D. Johnson.  Attorney Emily Hynek in court for State of Wisconsin. Defendant accepts his attorney appearing by zoom. State calls witness Deputy J Haag; sworn, testifies. Employed at the Jackson County as a Deputy. Testified to being on duty 9/28/22. Met w/victim 1's family. Located defendant. Record reflects identification. Aware defendant on bond conditions in other counties. State presents Exhibits 1 & 2, bonds from Eau Claire County. Court receives Exhibits 1 & 2. No objection. Attorney Swank cross-examines. Redirect. Re-cross. State rests. No other witnesses. Brief arguments. State makes argument, requests bind over. Defense makes argument, asks the court to dismiss counts 1,2 & 4. Court finds probable cause.

10:44 AM Defendant Skipper D. Johnson in court.  Attorney Lucas Swank appeared by video for Skipper D. Johnson.  Attorney Emily Hynek in court for State of Wisconsin. Defense makes motion to modify bond. State objects. Court denies motion.
Received e-mail from Attorney Plank requesting to appear via Zoom due to scheduling issues. Approved. Defendant will appear in-person for the hearings.
